    question: "What is `<!DOCTYPE html>` in HTML5?",
    answer: "The `<!DOCTYPE html>` declaration is the first line in an HTML document that tells the browser which version of HTML the page is written in.\n\n**Purpose:**\n• Ensures the browser renders the page in standards mode (not quirks mode)\n• In HTML5, it's the shortest and simplest doctype declaration\n• Must be declared at the very top of the HTML document\n\n**Example:**\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n    <title>My Page</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <!-- content -->\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n**Key Points:**\n• Case-insensitive (can be lowercase or uppercase)\n• Not an HTML tag, but an instruction to the browser\n• Without it, browsers may render pages in \"quirks mode\" causing layout issues",
