    question: "What is the difference between CSS and CSS3?",
    answer: "**CSS vs CSS3:**\n\n**CSS (CSS2.1):**\n• Released in 1998\n• Basic styling capabilities\n• Limited selectors\n• No media queries for responsive design\n• No animations/transitions\n• No rounded corners or shadows\n\n**CSS3:**\n• Modular approach (Selectors, Box Model, Backgrounds, etc.)\n• Enhanced capabilities\n\n**CSS3 New Features:**\n\n**1. Selectors:**\n```css\n/* New pseudo-classes */\n:first-of-type, :last-of-type, :nth-child()\n:not(), :is(), :where()\n```\n\n**2. Box Model Enhancements:**\n```css\n/* Border radius - rounded corners */\nborder-radius: 10px;\n\n/* Box shadow */\nbox-shadow: 5px 5px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);\n\n/* Gradients */\nbackground: linear-gradient(to right, red, blue);\n```\n\n**3. Animations & Transitions:**\n```css\n/* Transitions */\ntransition: all 0.3s ease;\n\n/* Keyframe animations */\n@keyframes slide {\n    from { transform: translateX(0); }\n    to { transform: translateX(100px); }\n}\n```\n\n**4. Flexbox & Grid:**\n```css\n/* Flexbox - 1D layout */\ndisplay: flex;\n\n/* Grid - 2D layout */\ndisplay: grid;\n```\n\n**5. Media Queries:**\n```css\n@media (max-width: 768px) {\n    /* Responsive styles */\n}\n```\n\n**6. Variables (Custom Properties):**\n```css\n:root {\n    --primary-color: #007bff;\n}\n\n.element {\n    color: var(--primary-color);\n}\n```\n\n**7. Web Fonts:**\n```css\n@font-face {\n    font-family: 'MyFont';\n    src: url('font.woff2');\n}\n```",
