    question: "What is media query in CSS?",
    answer: "**Media Queries:**\nCSS technique for responsive web design that applies styles based on device characteristics.\n\n**Syntax:**\n```css\n@media media-type and (condition) {\n    /* CSS rules */\n}\n```\n\n**Media Types:**\n• `all` - All devices (default)\n• `screen` - Computer screens, tablets, phones\n• `print` - Print preview mode\n• `speech` - Screen readers\n\n**Common Conditions:**\n\n**1. Viewport Width:**\n```css\n/* Mobile first */\n@media (min-width: 768px) { /* Tablet+ styles */ }\n\n/* Desktop first */\n@media (max-width: 768px) { /* Mobile styles */ }\n\n/* Range */\n@media (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 1024px) { /* Tablet */ }\n```\n\n**2. Device Orientation:**\n```css\n@media (orientation: landscape) { /* Landscape styles */ }\n@media (orientation: portrait) { /* Portrait styles */ }\n```\n\n**3. Resolution:**\n```css\n@media (min-resolution: 2dppx) { /* High DPI screens */ }\n```\n\n**4. Aspect Ratio:**\n```css\n@media (aspect-ratio: 16/9) { /* 16:9 screens */ }\n```\n\n**5. Dark/Light Mode:**\n```css\n@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) { /* Dark mode styles */ }\n@media (prefers-color-scheme: light) { /* Light mode styles */ }\n```\n\n**6. Reduced Motion:**\n```css\n@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {\n    * { animation: none; }\n}\n```\n\n**Example:**\n```css\n/* Responsive grid */\n.container {\n    display: grid;\n    grid-template-columns: 1fr;\n}\n\n@media (min-width: 768px) {\n    .container {\n        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);\n    }\n}\n\n@media (min-width: 1024px) {\n    .container {\n        grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);\n    }\n}\n```",
