    id: 20,
    level: "basic",
    topic: "CSS",
    category: "css",
    question: "What is pseudo selector in CSS?",
    answer: "**Pseudo Selectors:**\nKeywords added to selectors that specify a special state of the selected element.\n\n**Pseudo-classes (one colon :):**\nTarget element states.\n\n**1. Dynamic Pseudo-classes:**\n```css\n/* Link states */\na:link { }        /* Unvisited link */\na:visited { }     /* Visited link */\na:hover { }       /* Mouse over */\na:active { }      /* Click moment */\n\n/* Focus states */\ninput:focus { }   /* Input focused */\nbutton:focus-visible { } /* Focus with keyboard */\n```\n\n**2. Structural Pseudo-classes:**\n```css\n/* Child-based */\n:first-child { }   /* First child element */\n:last-child { }    /* Last child element */\n:nth-child(2) { }  /* Second child */\n:nth-child(odd) { } /* Odd children */\n:nth-child(even) { } /* Even children */\n:nth-child(3n) { } /* Every 3rd child */\n\n/* Type-based */\n:first-of-type { }  /* First of its type */\n:last-of-type { }   /* Last of its type */\n:nth-of-type(2) { } /* Second of its type */\n\n/* Other */\n:only-child { }     /* Only child element */\n:empty { }          /* Elements with no children */\n:root { }           /* Root element (html) */\n```\n\n**3. Form Pseudo-classes:**\n```css\n:checked { }      /* Checked checkbox/radio */\n:disabled { }     /* Disabled inputs */\n:enabled { }      /* Enabled inputs */\n:required { }     /* Required fields */\n:optional { }     /* Optional fields */\n:valid { }        /* Valid input */\n:invalid { }      /* Invalid input */\n:in-range { }     /* Value in range */\n:out-of-range { } /* Value out of range */\n```\n\n**4. Logical Pseudo-classes:**\n```css\n:not(.class) { }   /* Not matching selector */\n:is(h1, h2, h3) { } /* Any of selectors */\n:where(.class) { } /* Low specificity version of :is() */\n:has(img) { }      /* Element containing img (modern) */\n```\n\n**Pseudo-elements (two colons ::):**\nTarget specific parts of an element.\n\n```css\n/* Text pseudo-elements */\n::first-line { }    /* First line of text */\n::first-letter { }  /* First letter */\n::selection { }     /* Selected text */\n\n/* Content pseudo-elements */\n::before { }        /* Insert before content */\n::after { }         /* Insert after content */\n\n/* Other */\n::placeholder { }   /* Input placeholder */\n::marker { }        /* List markers */\n```\n\n**Examples:**\n```css\n/* Styling links */\na:hover {\n    color: red;\n    text-decoration: underline;\n}\n\n/* Alternating row colors */\ntr:nth-child(even) {\n    background-color: #f2f2f2;\n}\n\n/* Add icon before links */\na[href^=\"https\"]::before {\n    content: \"🔒 \";\n}\n\n/* Required field indicator */\ninput:required::after {\n    content: \" *\";\n    color: red;\n}\n\n/* Custom checkbox */\ninput[type=\"checkbox\"]:checked + label {\n    color: green;\n}\n```",
    tags: ["pseudo-selector", "pseudo-class", "pseudo-element", "css"]
