    category: "js",
    question: "Explain different types of function in JavaScript",
    answer: "**Types of Functions in JavaScript:**\n\n**1. Function Declaration:**\n```javascript\n// Hoisted - can be called before definition\nfunction greet(name) {\n    return `Hello, ${name}!`;\n}\n\nconsole.log(greet('John')); // \"Hello, John!\"\n```\n\n**2. Function Expression:**\n```javascript\n// Not hoisted\nconst greet = function(name) {\n    return `Hello, ${name}!`;\n};\n\nconsole.log(greet('John')); // \"Hello, John!\"\n```\n\n**3. Arrow Function (ES6):**\n```javascript\n// Concise syntax\nconst greet = (name) => `Hello, ${name}!`;\n\n// No arguments binding\nconst noArgs = () => 'Hello';\n\n// Single parameter - parentheses optional\nconst greet = name => `Hello, ${name}!`;\n\n// Multiple statements need braces and return\nconst calculate = (a, b) => {\n    const result = a + b;\n    return result;\n};\n\n// Lexical 'this' binding\nconst obj = {\n    name: 'John',\n    regular: function() {\n        setTimeout(function() {\n            console.log(this.name); // undefined (wrong this)\n        }, 100);\n    },\n    arrow: function() {\n        setTimeout(() => {\n            console.log(this.name); // 'John' (correct this)\n        }, 100);\n    }\n};\n```\n\n**4. Immediately Invoked Function Expression (IIFE):**\n```javascript\n// Executes immediately\n(function() {\n    console.log('IIFE executed');\n})();\n\n// With parameters\n(function(name) {\n    console.log(`Hello, ${name}`);\n})('John');\n\n// Arrow function IIFE\n(() => console.log('Arrow IIFE'))();\n\n// Creates private scope\nconst counter = (function() {\n    let count = 0;\n    return {\n        increment: () => ++count,\n        decrement: () => --count,\n        getCount: () => count\n    };\n})();\n```\n\n**5. Constructor Function:**\n```javascript\nfunction Person(name, age) {\n    this.name = name;\n    this.age = age;\n    this.greet = function() {\n        return `Hello, I'm ${this.name}`;\n    };\n}\n\nconst john = new Person('John', 25);\nconsole.log(john.greet()); // \"Hello, I'm John\"\n```\n\n**6. Class Method (ES6):**\n```javascript\nclass Person {\n    constructor(name, age) {\n        this.name = name;\n        this.age = age;\n    }\n    \n    greet() {\n        return `Hello, I'm ${this.name}`;\n    }\n    \n    static create(name) {\n        return new Person(name, 0);\n    }\n}\n\nconst john = new Person('John', 25);\nconsole.log(john.greet()); // \"Hello, I'm John\"\n```\n\n**7. Generator Function:**\n```javascript\nfunction* generator() {\n    yield 1;\n    yield 2;\n    yield 3;\n}\n\nconst gen = generator();\nconsole.log(gen.next().value); // 1\nconsole.log(gen.next().value); // 2\nconsole.log(gen.next().value); // 3\n\n// Infinite generator\nfunction* idGenerator() {\n    let id = 1;\n    while (true) {\n        yield id++;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**8. Async Function:**\n```javascript\nasync function fetchData() {\n    try {\n        const response = await fetch('https://api.example.com');\n        const data = await response.json();\n        return data;\n    } catch (error) {\n        console.error(error);\n    }\n}\n\n// Arrow async\nconst fetchData = async () => {\n    const data = await apiCall();\n    return data;\n};\n```\n\n**9. Recursive Function:**\n```javascript\nfunction factorial(n) {\n    if (n <= 1) return 1;\n    return n * factorial(n - 1);\n}\n\nconsole.log(factorial(5)); // 120\n\n// Tail recursion optimization\nfunction factorial(n, accumulator = 1) {\n    if (n <= 1) return accumulator;\n    return factorial(n - 1, n * accumulator);\n}\n```\n\n**10. Callback Function:**\n```javascript\nfunction processUserInput(callback) {\n    const name = prompt('Enter your name:');\n    callback(name);\n}\n\nprocessUserInput((name) => {\n    console.log(`Hello, ${name}!`);\n});\n```\n\n**11. Higher-Order Function:**\n```javascript\nfunction multiplier(factor) {\n    return function(x) {\n        return x * factor;\n    };\n}\n\nconst double = multiplier(2);\nconsole.log(double(5)); // 10\n```\n\n**12. Pure Function:**\n```javascript\n// Pure - no side effects, same input = same output\nfunction add(a, b) {\n    return a + b;\n}\n\n// Impure - has side effects\nlet count = 0;\nfunction increment() {\n    count++;\n    return count;\n}\n```\n\n**Comparison Table:**\n| Type | Hoisting | 'this' binding | Syntax | Use Case |\n|------|----------|----------------|--------|----------|\n| Declaration | Yes | Dynamic | function fn() | General |\n| Expression | No | Dynamic | const fn = function() | Conditional |\n| Arrow | No | Lexical | () => {} | Callbacks, 'this' binding |\n| IIFE | N/A | Depends | (function() {})() | Module pattern |\n| Generator | No | Dynamic | function* fn() | Iterators |\n| Async | No | Dynamic | async function | Async operations |",
    tags: ["functions", "arrow-functions", "generator", "async", "iife"]
